			What is SustainiCal?
		</div>
		<div class="about-detail">
			SustainiCal is hosting a <b>yearly competition</b> between UC Berkeley students by comparing their dorm-wide and unit-wide energy usage throughout the school year. This website can <b>track electricity and water usage</b> between the various dorms and compare those values to previous years as well as to <b>sustainable</b> levels. The competition will pit dorms against each other, and give <b>a major prize at the end of the semester</b> to whichever dorm shows the most improvement, along with smaller awards throughout the semester. Additionally, we hope to include intermittent goals and prizes for dorms to reward progress. We aim to give students several potential sources of motivation. Beyond energy and water usage, we are including other potential ways to understand and limit individual carbon footprints so that users won't simply focus on one aspect while ignoring other lifestyle choices. In doing so, we hope to <b>encourage a behavior change</b> in which students have a better understanding of their impact, carrying that knowledge into new communities beyond their freshman year.
		</div>	
